<subsection xml:id="subsec-Reading-and-writing-numbers-in-words">
          <title>Reading and writing numbers in words.</title>
          <activity>
            <statement>
              <p>
                
              </p>
              <p>
                A customer wanted to deposit the cheque below and did not know the cheque worth.
              </p>
              <image source="cheque.jpeg">
                <shortdescription></shortdescription>
              </image>
              <p>
                1. Help the customer to read and write the value of the cheque in words.
              </p>
              <p>
               2. Prepare dummy cheques similar to the one above.
              </p>
              <p>
                3. Fill in the dummy cheques you have created with amounts of your choice and it should be a 6-digit number.
              </p>
              <p>
                4. Read the amounts to your fellow learners.
              </p>
            </statement>
          </activity>
      <example>
      <statement>
        <p>
          The number of people who attended a cancer screening campaign in 2023 was 8 759 125. Read and write this number in words.

        </p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
        <p>
          Separate the digits in groups of threes starting from the ones place value. Write the total of each group.
        </p>
        <p>
          <m>8\,759\,125</m> = <m>8\,000\,000+ 759\,000 +125</m>
        </p>
        <p>
         <m>8\,759\,125</m> is Eight million, seven hundred and fifty nine thousand, one hundred and twenty five.
        </p>
      </solution>
  
     </example>
     <example>
      <statement>
        <p>
          The price of a certain car in Kenya is <m>3\,515\,252</m> shillings. Write the price of the car in words.
        </p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
        <p>
          Use the concept of place value and total value as illustrated below to write the amount in words.
        </p>
        <tabular bottom="medium" top="medium" right="medium" left="medium">
          <row header="yes">
            <cell>Digit</cell>
            <cell>Place value</cell>
            <cell>Total value</cell>
            <cell>Total value in words</cell>
          </row>
          <row>
            <cell>3</cell>
            <cell>Millions</cell>
            <cell><m>3\,000\,000</m></cell>
            <cell>Three million</cell>
          </row>
          <row>
            <cell>5</cell>
            <cell>Hundreds of thousands</cell>
            <cell><m>500\,000</m></cell>
            <cell>Five hundred thousand</cell>
          </row>
          <row>
            <cell>1</cell>
            <cell>Tens of thousands</cell>
            <cell><m>10\,000</m></cell>
            <cell>Ten thousand</cell>
          </row>
          <row>
            <cell>5</cell>
            <cell>Thousands</cell>
            <cell>5 000</cell>
            <cell>Five thousand</cell>
          </row>
          <row>
            <cell>2</cell>
            <cell>Hundreds</cell>
            <cell><m>200</m></cell>
            <cell>Two hundred</cell>
          </row>
          <row>
            <cell>5</cell>
            <cell>Tens</cell>
            <cell><m>50</m></cell>
            <cell>Fifty</cell>
          </row>
          <row>
            <cell>2</cell>
            <cell>Ones</cell>
            <cell>2</cell>
            <cell>Two</cell>
          </row>
        </tabular>
        <p>
          The price of the car in words is three million, five hundred and fifteen thousand, two hundred and fifty two.
        </p>
      </solution>
     </example>
